The paper presents a control approach for autonomous vehicles based on deep reinforcement learning, which involves training a neural network agent to map its estimated state to acceleration and steering commands given the objective of reaching a specific target state while considering detected obstacles. This work involves several aspects of computer science, including artificial intelligence (AI) for the neural network agent, robotics (RO) for the autonomous vehicle, machine learning (LG) for the deep reinforcement learning approach, systems and control (SY) for the control approach, and computer vision (CV) for obstacle detection. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.SY, and cs.CV, in that order.
